text: Carneades vittata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Gahan in 1889. It is known from Brazil, Ecuador, Bolivia, and Peru.BioLib.cz - Carneades vittata. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Colobotheini Category:Beetles described in 1889
title: Carneades vittata
